opmode.help: This page is used to change Operation Mode.
opmode.gateway_mode_msg: In this mode, the device is supposed to connect to internet via ADSL/Cable Modem. The NAT is enabled and PCs in LAN ports share the same IP to ISP through WAN port. The connection type can be setup in WAN page by using PPPOE, DHCP client, Static IP.
opmode.bridge_mode_msg: In this mode,connect the superior AP/Router by wire, you can bridge the superior's AP/Router wired signal into wireless Wi-Fi signals for Wi-Fi devices.
opmode.repeater_mode_msg: In this mode,you can extend the superior Wi-Fi signal by Repeater setting function under the Wireless column to increase the coverage of the wireless signal.
opmode.wisp_mode_msg: In this mode, all ethernet ports are bridged together and the wireless client will connect to ISP access point. The NAT is enabled and PCs in ethernet ports share the same IP to ISP through wireless LAN.
opmode.select_ap: Please select a list of sites that need to be relayed!
opmode.aplist_help: Please select a list of sites that need to be relayed. Tip: Click the Scan?button to search for the current AP site.
opmode.aplist_help1: If the upward AP is encrypted, please fill in the correct password and click 'Connect'; If the upward AP is not encrypted, click 'Connect' directly.

net_strategy.help: This page is used to set the networking strategy.
net_strategy.lan_conflict: Connected IP address conflict! Please change the IP segment on the "{0}" page
net_strategy.wan_conflict: Connected IP address conflict! Please modify the network segment for upstream route allocation IP
net_strategy.tips1: A device set to "Slave mode" can dial to a device set to "Master mode" for remote networking
net_strategy.tips2: Device identification name of the current device in the remote network
net_strategy.tips3: The unique identification of the entire network in the remote network, usually as a sign for the slave device to find the master device network in the entire WAN
net_strategy.tips4: Security identification means for accessing the network of the main device. In order to enhance security, it is designed to have a password corresponding to one device. Other devices cannot reuse the password. Special reminder: please do not set the same after the password is deleted Password.
net_strategy.tips5: Custom exit or entrance for network data traffic, please keep the default settings for non-special needs
net_strategy.tips6: Control user access to a certain subnet, for users with high demand, it is not necessary to set items

fota.help: To upgrade Hisense mnr02 module FOTA, please first confirm that the network connection is normal during the upgrade.
